					"body": "Note: Due to SDK limitations, this will work only for Widgets exposing one of the supported View classes, see list at http://docs.appcelerator.com/titanium/latest/#!/api/Titanium.UI.ListItem",
					"updateAuthor": {
						"name": "skypanther",
						"key": "skypanther",
						"displayName": "Tim Poulsen",
						"active": true,
						"timeZone": "America/New_York"
					},
					"created": "2015-01-07T14:30:14.000+0000",
					"updated": "2015-01-07T14:30:14.000+0000"
				},
				{
					"id": "406417",
					"author": {
						"name": "BBMobileDev",
						"key": "bbmobiledev",
						"displayName": "Blackbaud MobileDev",
						"active": true,
						"timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
					},
					"body": "The deeper problem is that even if your widget's top level view is a ListItem. You still cannot have Widget tags inside of that list item. This still crashes the compiler. Thus you can't use widgets in a ListView :( which limits the re-usability of your widget functionality.",
